$ rsync options source destination
rsync -azv /var/opt/installation/inventory/ 10.251.16.100:/root/temp/ --progress
rsync -azv /var/opt/installation/inventory/ username@10.251.16.100:/root/temp/

*** N.B. -z option will decrease the copying speed.

rsync option -a indicates archive mode. -a option does the following
Recursive mode
Preserves symbolic links
Preserves permissions
Preserves timestamp
Preserves owner and group

-z, --compress              compress file data during the transfer


** Best Practice **
nohup rsync -az /poarchive/ 10.251.16.xx:/poarchive/ &

** never use -v in nohup as nohup.out file will increase continuously.


otherwise nohup.out inside /root directories will increase
rsync -av --exclude='*.txt' original/ duplicate/

find /root/RAJSEKHORE/fol5/folB/ -type f | xargs -n 1 -P 2 -I{} rsync -av {} /root/ram/sajal/

find fi2el6ilvmi67kj7aaaacyb24h/ -type f | xargs -n 1 -I{} rsync -av {} /backup_new/Test/sajal/

find 05/fi2el6ilvmi67kj7aaaacyb24h/ -type f | xargs -n 10 -P 4 -I{} rsync -av --ignore-existing {} /opt/test/
